To bring up two files in split form:

vim -o filename1  filename2

Once you are in use ctl-w and the arrow keys to move back and forth.

Use ctl-w  shift L  to make the windows next to each other from side-by-side.

The help command for working  in windows while you are in windows is :help windows.


zg adds word to spelling list

F7 toggles between spell check mode (see .vimrc for the setup)

]s goes to next mis-spelled word

